Common.LongDescription.Common.Text:
10 Hobart Place comprises a striking 8-storey commercial office building totaling 4,500sqm of lettable area and positioned within the vibrant City West CBD precinct. An extensive refurbishment of the building has now been completed, with a brand new fitted out tenancy delivering modern office space that features an industrial style aesthetic. The building provides occupiers exceptional tenant amenity with new End of Trip facilities and onsite café. 10 Hobart Place has a 0 NABERS Energy rating.

The building is situated in the heart of the legal precinct. Conveniently located adjacent to a multi storey car park and located within proximity to major public transport links and arterial roads for easy access, as well as the cream of Canberra's cafes, restaurants, bars and retail amenities.

Completed Refurbishment Works:

• Cosmetic upgrade to main entry foyer including new directory board & building exterior
• Cosmetic upgrade to lift lobbies on each floor
• Cosmetic upgrade to lift cart interiors
• Upgrades to base building services including new tenant switch boards & Chiller
• Refurbished office floors featuring exposed ceiling services, polished concrete floors and glass internal corridor partitioning
• New End of Trip facilities including separate male and female showers, lockers and change rooms.
• New secure bike storage in the basement of the building

Available:

Level 7:  110sqm* (brand new fit out including waiting area, breakout area, meeting room, collaboration space and open plan workspace accommodating 10 workstations).

Approx.

For more information on 10 Hobart Place or to arrange an inspection please contact CBRE Canberra.

Common.PostalAddresses.Common.Line1: Former Muddle Bar Premises, 8 West Row
Former Muddle Bar Premises, 8 West Row

Common.LongDescription.Common.Text:
Situated amongst an array of well-known eateries and drink establishments, this property is superbly located to attract those who live and work in Canberra's CBD.

The property is located within the iconic Melbourne Building sitting between the popular Mezzalira Ristorante and Thirst Thai Restaurant, and opposite the new Mayfair Apartments.

In addition to the mixed use residential/office/retail surroundings, the property is also within walking distance to the Canberra Theatre, Museum, Gallery and the Canberra Centre.

The property's former use as a drink establishment (known as Muddle Bar) means the property includes a swanky cocktail bar fitout so the incoming occupier can get immediate access and start serving cocktails.

The Crown Lease also permits a range of allowable uses (including but not limited to office, shop and health facility) so you don't have to be in the hospitality industry to take advantage of this excellent real estate opportunity.

Baileys Corner is a predominant City landmark located on London Circuit. This location is perfect for both retail and offices with a high flow of foot traffic daily. The ground floor consists of retail tenancies with only 1 space currently available for lease. The first floor consists of boutique office space with only 1 space currently available. The list of these tenancies is outlined below.

1st Floor -  Office 5 - 56.30sqm*
1st Floor -  Office 8 - 42.20sqm* (can be combined with 9 & 10) - fitout 2x offices with glass partitioning
1st Floor -  Office 9 - 84.40sqm* (can be combined with suites 8 & 10
1st Floor -  Office 10 - 58.00sqm* (can be combined with 8 & 9) - fitout 3x offices with glass partitioning

Contact CBRE for further information or to arrange an inspection.
